     "group": "Separation of data flows",
     "name": "overview",
     "prose": {
      "en": "To ensure that data flows are appropriately controlled within CDSs, it is important that isolated upward and downward network paths are implemented. This, in turn, should be supported by independent security-enforcing functions and protocol breaks at each network layer."
     }
